then theres so biom disitruibution which is nich but i dont plan on being to fancy with the placement s of biomes in my game.

then he provides us caves which look cool but i'm not exactly looking for that kind of generation. however if your intreated on how they do it. it's a perlin2d line that super imposed on the terrain you alreay generated. However what i beilie is better to show cave genertion is something that i'll be using thats called tile runner. kind of like ants, the tile runner starts randomly at the surface then takes random paterrns going deeper in the surface. It's really really cool and i think you should check it out. "https://forum.gamemaker.io/index.php?threads/randomly-generated-terrain-using-tile-runners.53100/" This way i can limit the radius, lenth and number of caves i get instead of using the other method. Anyways continuing on with "jefferey morray".he goes in to a lot more detail about biomes transitioning. This is  imoprotant as providing a smooth transition is nessart to the feel and look of a game however i'c completly lost here and have no clue waht this means :

